value: Known to breed in southwestern Siberia on the upper Irtysh and about Lake Tschany; thought to breed on the upper Ob and in the Turgai dis- trict. Winters in the countries bordering the Mediterranean. Occurs on migration in eastern Europe, Transcaspia and Persia.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, coastal areas: Morocco, Tunisia.
Boggy areas in steppe country (breeding); mudflats, beaches, marshes, and wet fields (nonbreeding).
bogs, swampy steppe, marshy forest edge, migrn beaches, mudflats
